Class BigSplitPackedArray

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.PrimitiveCollection
      • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.PrimitiveArray
        • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.PrimitiveSplitArray
          • com.telenav.kivakit.core.collections.primitive.array.packed.BigSplitPackedArray
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.esotericsoftware.kryo.KryoSerializable, PackedPrimitiveArray, Initializable, NamedObject, Countable, Sized, CompressibleCollection
    public class BigSplitPackedArray
extends PrimitiveSplitArray
implements PackedPrimitiveArray
    BigSplitPackedArray maintains an array of packed arrays, indexing them as a single larger array. The purpose in this is to avoid resizing as a very large packed array grows. Instead, when a write index is greater than the size of the BigSplitPackedArray, a new PackedArray is allocated and added to the list. This design is similar to the "rope" pattern for handling very large strings.
    Author:
    jonathanl (shibo)
